Class WorldDataUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.WorldDataUtils

  • public class WorldDataUtils
extends java.lang.Object

    WorldDataUtils

    A Utility class made for the Data Entries from the World Data Bank Site.

    • Makes Country Code Map for the world data bank for a certain year
    • Make Markers for World Data Bank entries
    • Make PointFeatures for Cities on Map
    • Make PointFeatures for Countries on Map
    • Make Markers for Cities on Map
    • Make Markers for Countries on Map
    • Checks if a Point Feature is on land or not
    • Checks if a Point Feature

    Since:
    21/7/2019

      • toCountryCodeMap

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> toCountryCodeMap(java.lang.Iterable<? extends WorldData> data,
                                                                               int year)
        Takes the Iterable of WorldData Records and uses it to output a Map. where key is Country Code and Value is Life Expectancy for given year parameter that will be used by the Map with Geographical locations to make a map out of it with needed value is values for the given year
        Parameters:
        data - Iterable holding type of WorldData holding data of each record in the parsed CSV file
        year - needed for the values, must be valid year between 1960 to 2017 inclusive
        Returns:
        Map containing Country Code as its key and needed Value as it's value
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if No Applet is used by the class or data given is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if year isn't between 1960 to 2017

      • makeWorldDataMarkers

        public static java.util.List<de.fhpotsdam.unfolding.marker.Marker> makeWorldDataMarkers(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> map,
                                                                                        float inputRangeStart,
                                                                                        float inputRangeEnd)
        Makes markers Method that takes the current PApplet, map that will be used to make markers from. using the country and it's value key: Country ID and float value as Value assigned to that country id initializes the countryFeatures List of the WorldDataUtils once as it's the same for all data holding points for each place on the map using the JSON object data that holds all locations of Map and ID element for each location matching the one in the Map sent , to color the markers with shades of blue and red using the matching ID value with year expectancy then shading the colors of the markers made
        Parameters:
        map - Map that holds the country code and value associated to it
        inputRangeStart - float that represents the starting value of the input range that the value of map is in to be mapped to a valie between 0 to 255
        inputRangeEnd - float that represents the ending value of the input range that the value of map is in to be mapped to a valie between 0 to 255
        Returns:
        List of Markers due to the given Map containing countries and their values due to World Bank
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if No Applet is used by the class or data given is null

      • isLand

        public static boolean isLand(de.fhpotsdam.unfolding.data.PointFeature location)
        Checks whether a PointFeature is on land or not A location is on land if it's in some country, luckily we have a List representing countries locations as features so we can use it, to determine that an earthquake which is represented as a pointfeature is in a country or not, returning true or false note that some countries are made into multimarkers (markrers represented on a big area and some are made ) into simplePolygon markers that represents also an area this is implemented in UnfoldingMap API for ease of use so we have to check if the feature is in a marker country and a marker country can be multimarker or simple polygon marker so we have to check for both, note: multimarker holds markers and u can get it using .getMarkers(), note that AbstractShape Marker is the superclass of polygon marker countries markers are made of SimplePolygonMarker or MultiMarkers a MultiMarker in case of the countries marker , holds logically grouped markers for a certain country, so basically multimarker is a container of logical related markers a country can be implemented using a multimarker holding simple polygon shape marker or a direct simple polygon shape marker due to the country features being a simplePolygonFeature or a MultiFeature due to geoJSON implementation in unfolding map List can hold both loops over the country markers made by the List of countries from geoReader checking if one of them returns true to that location, this is done by looping over each marker in the countryMarkers and checking if the location is inside the marker location using the isInCountry private method
        Parameters:
        location - PointFeature of location
        Returns:
        True if PointFeature is on land, false otherwise
